The ellipses in Eq.(3.5) represent appropriately contracted Lorentz indices, which we suppress. We note that the M terms originate from the mass left-overs of Eq.(2.6). The factors B and M in the expressions above are in general complicated functions of q, p1, and p2, and boson masses; however they do not depend on the individual momenta and masses of the external "test" fermions. Notice also that they are ultra-violet finite since they originated from box diagrams. Clearly, the B's or the M's may be zero for

