In this last expression the ,-dependence is carried solely by the tree-level Goldstone boson propagators \Delta OE(q; ,W ). The requirement that ^T1 is ,-independent, gives rise to two independent equations; the first enforces the cancellation of the terms with only one \Delta OE factor, whereas the second enforces the cancellation of the terms with a \Delta OE \Delta OE factor. It is then a matter of simple algebra to show that the following WI should hold [33] :

